description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an ideal opportunity for an experienced registered pharmacy technician to work as an ACPT and gain skills in staff management and service development in a busy hospital pharmacy department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The position for a Senior Pharmacy Technician for Patient Services requires a proactive and dynamic individual to work closely with peers and dispensary management to uphold the high standards of patient care and medicines optimisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alongside the accuracy checking responsibility, the post holder will have a leadership role which includes supporting with the day to day smooth running of the dispensary, training staff through supervision and monitoring performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate must be registered with the GPhC and be experienced in accuracy checking with a nationally recognised qualification. Further training will be provided on staff management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Shaista Raja Job title Principal Pharmacist Planned Care, Women and Children&lt;/p&gt;
